revision.text:
{{Infobox film | name = 12/12/12 | image = Evil Born poster.jpg | alt = | caption = Film poster | director = [[Jared Cohn]] |producers = {{ubl|[[David Michael Latt]]|[[Paul Bales]]}} | writer = | screenplay = Jared Cohn | story = | based on = | starring = {{ubl|[[Sara Malakul Lane]]|[[Jesus Guevara]]|[[Erin O'Brien (actress)|Erin O'Brien]]|Steve Hanks|Carl Donelson}} | narrator = | music = Graham Denman | cinematography = Ben Demaree | editing = Andre Law | studio = [[The Asylum]] | distributors = {{ubl|The Asylum|Peacock Films|Schröder Media}} | released = {{film date|2012|12|4|DVD}} | runtime = 86 minutes | country = United States | language = English | budget = | gross = }} '''''12/12/12''''' (also known as '''''Evil Born''''') is a 2012 American [[horror film]] written and directed by [[Jared Cohn]]. It was filmed in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]] and released on December 4, 2012.<ref name="Dread Central"/><ref name="28 Days Later">{{cite web|last=Allen|first=Michael|title=Nothing Happens in The Asylum's 12/12/12: A Movie Review|url=http://www.28dayslateranalysis.com/2012/12/nothing-happens-in-asylums-121212-movie.html|publisher=28dayslateranalysis.com|accessdate=17 December 2013}}</ref><ref name="OFDB">{{cite web|title=Kritik: A Retro Kinski bespricht Evil Born (2012)|url=http://en.ofdb.de/review/232877,557884,Evil-Born|language=German|publisher=Online Film Datenbank|accessdate=May 18, 2015|date=June 19, 2013}}</ref>
==Plot== The film begins with a baby, Sebastian, being born. After Sebastian viciously murders the doctors who delivered him, his mother ([[Sara Malakul Lane]]) realizes that there is something seriously wrong with the child (it is later revealed that he is the son of the devil). Over the course of the movie, Sebastian brutally murders many people and tragedy strikes many others. Mahari ([[Jesus Guevara]]) attempts to steal the baby from Sebastian's birth parents many times and eventually does. He steals Sebastian in order to embrace his evil calling. Police officers attempt to kill Mahari but Mahari and his companions use Sebastian to murder them. The movie ends with all the main characters dead, and their deaths were associated in some way to Sebastian.
==Cast== {{div col|colwidth=30em}} * [[Sara Malakul Lane]] as Veronica Alvarez * [[Jesus Guevara]] as Mahari * [[Erin O'Brien (actress)|Erin O'Brien]] as Nurse At Station * [[Steve Hanks]] as Detective Barnes * [[Carl Donelson]] as Carlos * [[Laura Ramos]] as Gabriella * [[Samantha Stewart]] as Officer Vokel * [[Rachel Alig]] as Katherine * [[Jared Cohn]] as Jared * Katy-Ann Thompson as Nurse Madysson * Gregory Niebel as Doctor Ulf * Shakira Ja'nai Paye as Kayla * Shauna Chin as Barbara * Jourdan Lee as Jason Tremmel * Jon Kondelik as Trevor * Samuel Fisher as Officer Kemp * Sam Ingraffia as Father Anders {{div col end}}
==Reception== {{expand section|date=May 2015}} ''[[Dread Central]]'' called it an "[[The Omen|Omen]]-esque horror flick titled after the date on which its hellspawn will be born".<ref name="Dread Central"/> Filming the project created controversy in Thailand, in which set photos showing Sara Malakul Lane in costume looking as if pregnant were mistakenly thought to be real, for there are cultural taboos there about unwed motherhood.<ref name="Dread Central">{{cite news|last1=Foy|first1=Scott|title=The Spawn of Satan Will be Born on 12-12-12 and We Have His Exclusive First Baby Photos|url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/36112/the-spawn-of-satan-will-be-born-on-12-12-12-and-we-have-his-exclusive-first-baby-photos/|accessdate=May 18, 2015|publisher=[[Dread Central]]|date=August 12, 2012}}</ref>
