{{Infobox video game |title = Death to Spies: Moment of Truth |image = Death to Spies-Moment of Truth Images poster.jpg |caption = Poster for ''Death to Spies: Moment of Truth'' |developer = Haggard Games |publisher = [[1C Company]] |series = [[Death to Spies]] |released = August 10, 2009 |genre = [[Stealth game|Stealth]] [[Action game|Action]] |modes = |platforms = [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] }}
'''''Death To Spies: Moment Of Truth''''' ({{lang-ru|Смерть шпионам: Момент истины|italic=yes}}) is a [[third-person shooter|third-person]] [[stealth game|stealth]] [[action game|action]] [[PC game]] set during [[World War II]]. Produced by [[1C Company]] along with Russian studio Haggard Games, ''Moment of Truth'' is a sequel to the stealth action ''[[Death to Spies]]''.
==Game Overview== The game's main character is Semion Strogov, who is a captain in the 4th department of the Soviet counterintelligence service called [[SMERSH]]. SMERSH is an acronym of the [[Russian language|Russian]] phrase ''Smert' Shpionam'', meaning 'Death to Spies', which was the name for a set of counterintelligence departments in the Soviet Army formed during World War II. Semion Strogov is back from his previous missions and must now participate in a series of even more complicated and exciting [[covert]] operations under the code name "Death to Spies: Moment of Truth". The hero possesses all the skills required to accomplish dangerous missions including getting information about the disposition of hostile military and civil units, and assassination of enemy agents and representatives of the [[Wehrmacht]]’s high-ranking officers and espionage. After having undergone some serious retraining, Semion Strogov will have to accomplish various top secret missions. His task is to capture spies, saboteurs and gather information about their actions using unique technologies and devices. The character's [[wikt:forte|forté]] is being able to carry out the operations with maximum stealth, using various techniques which include, but are not limited to: [[picking locks]], stunning or using chloroform on enemies, throwing knives, [[garroting]], [[booby trap]]s: setting traps on dead bodies, doors, etc.
==Game Features== *Reveals the activities of the mysterious [[SMERSH]] counterintelligence service of World War II,<ref name="Features">http://www.death2spies.com/?action=smersh_mi</ref> with missions based on actual historical facts and declassified data on the SMERSH.<ref name="Features"/> *Stealth action with sneaking, knife throwing, silent elimination of enemies, distracting enemies, picking locks, setting mines and other booby traps, covert observation and surveying.<ref name="Features"/> *Various World War II era vehicles, including cars and motorcycles.<ref name="Features"/>
==Sequel== {{main|Alekhine's Gun}} The third installment in the series was announced in 2010 by [[1C Company]] under the title ''Death to Spies 3: Ghost of Moscow'', which was being developed by Haggard Games.<ref name="1C">{{cite web |url=http://forum.1cpublishing.eu/showthread.php?t=15109 |title=Death To Spies 3 in Development |publisher=1C Company |date=6 October 2010 |accessdate=21 November 2015}}</ref> In 2011, 1C Company withdrew from the publishing contract, but Haggard Games continued developing the title. A crowdfunding campaign was launched on [[Indiegogo]] in 2013<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?id=243597542371781&story_fbid=507396925991840 |title=Facebook - DTS3 Indiegogo |publisher=Haggard Games |date=6 May 2013 |accessdate=21 November 2015}}</ref> and another on [[Kickstarter]] in 2014,<ref name="Kickstarter">{{cite web |url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/haggardgames/death-to-spies-3 |title=Death to Spies 3: Stealth Action, Hitman meets Splinter Cell |publisher=Kickstarter |date=17 October 2014 |accessdate=21 November 2015}}</ref> both of which failed. In June 2015, [[Maximum Games]] was announced as the new publisher and developer making it their first in-house game, renaming it to ''[[Alekhine's Gun]]'', which is a reference to the [[Alekhine's gun|chess formation]] of the same name.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.maximumgames.com/alekhines-gun/ |title=Alekhine's Gun |publisher=MaximumGames.com |accessdate=4 July 2015}}</ref> It saw the light of the day on multiple platforms ([[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]]) on 1 March 2016.
