{{distinguish|Hugo III, Jungle of Doom!}}
'''''Hugo: Jungle Island''''' is a defunct [[interactive television]] program that was an improved replacement to the early 1990s' original children's game show in the [[Hugo (franchise)|''Hugo'' franchise]]. It was originally launched by [[ITE Media]] in Denmark as ''Hugo Vulkanøen'' in January 1999, and was promptly licensed and broadcast in many other countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ite.dk/ite/frame/start3.htm |title=Interactive Television Entertainment |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010429153917/http://www.ite.dk/ite/frame/start3.htm |archivedate=April 29, 2001 }}</ref>
In this scenario, the evil nemesis of the friendly troll [[Hugo (troll)|Hugo]], the witch Scylla (Afskylia in the original Danish version), has returned and moved to a jungle island where she teamed up with the local tyrant Don Croco. Scylla once again kidnapped Hugo's wife Hugolina and the children, but this time she keeps them captive in a cage in her new lair, located at a top of volcano in the center of the island. The players control Hugo, aided by the monkey Jean Paul and the toucan Ferdinand, as he needs to complete a series [[minigame]]s ("hugocopter", ostrich jockey ride, liana climbing, volcano lava chase, etc.) to reach and defeat the witch and free his family.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ite.dk/?content=jungleTV.htm |title=ITE |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070218235919/http://www.ite.dk/?content=jungleTV.htm |archivedate=February 18, 2007 }}</ref>
==Video games== {{Infobox video game |title = Hugo: Jungle Island |image = |caption = |developer = [[ITE Media]] |publisher = ITE Media |released = 1999-2000,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hugoswelt.de/infos/historie/games/index.html|title=Games-Historie|author=Nico Schimmelpfennig}}</ref> 2004<ref name=pdf>[https://web.archive.org/web/20050404165156/http://www.ite.dk/newsletters/ITE_Newsletter_July.pdf]</ref> |genre = [[Action game|Action]], [[Puzzle video game|puzzle]] |modes = [[Single-player]] |platforms = [[Windows]] }}
A series of two video games based on it were released by ITE Media for the PC adaptation in 1999-2000,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hugoswelt.de/games/dschungelinsel/hugo7/index.php|title=Hugo 7 - Dschungelinsel|author=Nico Schimmelpfennig}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hugoswelt.de/games/dschungelinsel/hugo8/index.php|title=Hugo 8 - Dschungelinsel 2|author=Nico Schimmelpfennig}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bibliotek.dk/da/work/870970-basis:22591630|title=Hugo - Vulkanøen - bibliotek.dk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bibliotek.dk/da/work/870970-basis:23240041|title=Hugo - Vulkanøen 2 - bibliotek.dk}}</ref> followed by a third game in 2004.<ref name=pdf/> They were released under localized titles in various countries (such as ''Dschungelinsel'' in Germany and ''Tropikalna Wyspa'' in Poland).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gry-online.pl/S016.asp?ID=127|title=Hugo: Tropikalna Wyspa, Hugo: Jungle Island (PC) - GRY-Online.pl|work=GRY-Online.pl}}</ref> The ''Hugo: Jungle Island'' game series was generally well received.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesector.dk/2000/11/13/hugo-vulkanoen-2/|title=Hugo Vulkanøen 2|publisher=Gamesector.dk}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gry.wp.pl/recenzja/hugo-tropikalna-wyspa,220,1.html|title=Hugo: Tropikalna Wyspa|author=Grupa Wirtualna Polska|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gry-online.pl/S020.asp?ID=246|title=Hugo: Tropikalna Wyspa - recenzja gry|date=1 March 2001|work=GRY-Online.pl}}</ref> The first two games reached the top of PC sales charts in Turkey.<ref name=pdf/>
Their content was later effectively re-released as the fifth and sixth volume in the ''Hugo Classic'' series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hugoswelt.de/games/classic/classic5/index.php|title=Hugo Classic#5|author=Nico Schimmelpfennig}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hugoswelt.de/games/classic/classic6/index.php|title=Hugo Classic#6|author=Nico Schimmelpfennig}}</ref> Some of other Hugo game adaptations are also located on that island, including ''[[Hugo: Quest for the Sunstones]]'' and ''[[Hugo: Black Diamond Fever]]''.
